job.template: RequestCount = data("RequestCount", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)

metrics.description: HTTP 4XX and 5XX Error codes generated by the load balancer per minute

job.template:
HTTP4ERRORS_CLASSIC1 = data("HTTPCode_ELB_4xx", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
HTTP4ERRORS_APPLICATION1 = data("HTTPCode_ELB_4xx_Count", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ApplicationELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
HTTP_4xx_ERROR_SUM1  = (HTTP4ERRORS_CLASSIC1 + HTTP4ERRORS_APPLICATION1)
HTTP5ERRORS_CLASSIC1 = data("HTTPCode_ELB_5xx", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
HTTP5ERRORS_APPLICATION1 = data("HTTPCode_ELB_5xx_Count", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ApplicationELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
HTTP_5xx_ERROR_SUM1  = (HTTP5ERRORS_CLASSIC1 + HTTP5ERRORS_APPLICATION1)
HTTP_ERROR_SUM  = (HTTP_4xx_ERROR_SUM1 + HTTP_5xx_ERROR_SUM1)

metrics.description: Unhealthy Hosts / (Healthy Hosts + Unhealthy Hosts). Under 5% is Green, 5-20% Yellow, above 20% is Red

job.template:
HEALTHY_HOST_COUNT = data("HealthyHostCount", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "mean") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"])
UNHEALTHY_HOST_COUNT = data("UnHealthyHostCount", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "mean") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"])
UNHEALTHY_HOST_PERCENT = (UNHEALTHY_HOST_COUNT / (UNHEALTHY_HOST_COUNT + HEALTHY_HOST_COUNT)) * 100

metrics.description: Total elapsed time from the load-balancer sends request to when host responds (HTTP) or connection is established (TCP)

job.template: LATENCY = data("Latency", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "mean") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).mean(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(1000)

metrics.description: Pending requests since load-balancer was unable to establish a connection with a healthy hos (max: 1024)

job.template: SURGE_QUEUE_LENGTH = data("SurgeQueueLength", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "mean") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).mean(by=["LoadBalancerName"])

metrics.description: Error codes generated by the load balancer when a request is malformed or incomplete per minute

job.template:
HTTP4ERRORS_CLASSIC = data("HTTPCode_ELB_4xx", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
HTTP4ERRORS_APPLICATION = data("HTTPCode_ELB_4xx_Count", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ApplicationELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
HTTP_4xx_ERROR_SUM  = (HTTP4ERRORS_CLASSIC + HTTP4ERRORS_APPLICATION)

metrics.description: Error codes generated when there are no healthy instances registered to the load balancer, or if the request rate exceeds the capacity of the instances (spillover) or the load balancer, per minute

job.template:
HTTP5ERRORS_CLASSIC = data("HTTPCode_ELB_5xx", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
HTTP5ERRORS_APPLICATION = data("HTTPCode_ELB_5xx_Count", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ApplicationELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
HTTP_5xx_ERROR_SUM  = (HTTP5ERRORS_CLASSIC + HTTP5ERRORS_APPLICATION)

HEALTHY_HOST_COUNT1 = data("HealthyHostCount", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "mean") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"])

UNHEALTHY_HOST_COUNT1 = data("UnHealthyHostCount", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "mean") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"])

metrics.description: Number of connections that were not successfully established between the load balancer and target

job.template:
BACKEND_ERRORS_CLASSIC = data("BackendConnectionErrors", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
BACKEND_ERRORS_APPLICATION = data("TargetConnectionErrorCount", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ApplicationELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
BACKEND_ERRORS_SUM  = (BACKEND_ERRORS_CLASSIC + BACKEND_ERRORS_APPLICATION)

metrics.description: Requests that were rejected because the surge queue is full

job.template: SPILLOVER_COUNT = data("SpilloverCount", filter=filter("namespace", "AWS/ELB") and filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"])

metrics.description: Total number of HTTP responses including 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX errors per minute

job.template: RESPONSES_SUM = data("HTTPCode_*", filter=filter("stat", "sum") and filter("LoadBalancerName", "*"){{#filter}} and {{{filter}}}{{/filter}}, extrapolation="last_value", maxExtrapolations=2).sum(by=["LoadBalancerName"]).scale(60)
